(Fordgobike-tripdata Dataset)¶

by (Maryam Abdullah)¶

Introduction¶

In this investigation, I wanted to look at the history of Bike trips that could be used to enhance their values and user retention. The core focus was on user behavior and information about trips or users such as Gender, User type, Duration of the trip, start and end time for each trip.

What is the structure of your dataset?¶

The data consisted of approximately 183412 trip information described with 16 features. The attributes are related to two parts the trips and users. Further, most of the attributes are numeric and there is a time attribute with the wrong data type, also there are some of the columns has not clear purpose such as birth year so we can get valuable information in case we extracted the age from it. Also, we can dig deep into the duration in seconds and convert it into hours or minutes. As well as we can get the day with the most trips through extract weekday from the time attribute of starting or ending. In general, there is no duplicate value and this means each trip is unique however there are some missing data.

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

I will focus on analyzing each member's information like their type, and gender. Also, the trip's behavior like the duration in seconds, and starting time. Among all the previewed mention features, I am seeking to find the best attribute that effect trips to contribute to enhancing the use of bikes.

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

From the main feature above, I think the feature that will help in the further investigation is a birth year and starting/ending time because will extract from them more information like age, weekday, and hours of starting/ending.

Wrangling & Cleaning¶

Main quality issues need to be cleaned :¶

  • Change data type
  • Extract the hrs and day name -Extract the duration on hours and minutes
  • Find the age from the birth year
  • Drop unnecessary columns

def bar_catg(xvalue,order,titel,xlebel):
    plt.figure(figsize=[8, 5])
    sb.countplot(data = df, x = xvalue,order = order)
    plt.title(titel)
    plt.xlabel(xlebel) 
    plt.show();

Conclusions¶

At the end of this I observed many things related to the usage pattern For instance: we can increase profit if we focus on males because they are more than females in the dataset, also if we provided along with bike some comfortable stuff will attract more female since they bike for a long time.

We can see that we got more subscribers that used bikes but both of subscribers and customers share the same time to start their trip so we need to provide more bikes at the peak hour and afternoon. Also, we may offer more discounts or ads during the weekend to attract customers since they tend to use and spend more time biking during the weekend. The average duration for all trips is about 500 seconds, less than 15 minutes and 1 hour. So I assume they use it for near places only, and most trips were taken on Thursdays and Tuesdays.
